external_knowledge:
- "garden of the recent past month" refers to the activities recorded in the last month;
- "blooming boroughs" are boroughs that have had activity logs within the last month;
- "sprouting dates" refer to the establishment dates of the boroughs;
- "type of soil they thrive in" corresponds to the class name of the boroughs;
- "highest level of care they receive from gardeners" refers to the highest permission level associated with the boroughs;
- "sum of seeds planted across them" represents the total population of the boroughs.

- 'more populous and wealthy boroughs' refers to boroughs that are part of a class with higher than average population and median income;
- 'typical demographic details' include average values of population, median income, and population density;
- 'ranked from the most densely populated first' means ordering the results by descending population density.

sql:
SELECT full_name
FROM users
WHERE user_id = 1;

SELECT name, borough_seat
FROM boroughs
WHERE borough_id > 5 AND name LIKE 'A%';

SELECT boroughs.name, borough_boundaries.geometry
FROM boroughs
JOIN borough_boundaries ON boroughs.borough_id = borough_boundaries.borough_id;

